						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up against the wall (outside) of the house of Kōttapēṭa Venkaṭa Reḍḍi.</p>						

						<p>SADĀŚIVADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1542 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in Śaka 1466, Krōdhi corresponding to 1544 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Registers the remission of taxes on barbers of Maddikera by Śrīrangarāja Ayyavāru who was ruling from Jagatāpigutti.</p>						

						</summary>
